						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone at the gateway of the Banaśaṅkari temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Kannara—A.D. 1249.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1171, Kīlaka, Phālguṇa, śu. 7, Sunday</hi> in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Kaṁdhāradēva</hi> and corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1249, February 21, Sunday.</hi> The <hi rend="italic">Śaka</hi> year cited is the current year. </p>						

						<p>It states that a certain <hi rend="bold">Māyidēva</hi> made a gift of land to the temple of <hi rend="bold">Rāmanāthadēva. Ānevari</hi> (modern Hoḷi-Ānvēri) is mentioned. The inscription is very badly damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
